description: Archie takes over the comic book from The Shield

Archie takes over the book from The Shield.

1st appearance of Suzie in Pep Comics.
We see the early days of the most famous love triangle in comic book history on this cover.

Main features:

Oh, Weatherbee! - Archie / comic story / 10 pages - Archie dresses up as his Aunt Jane, who is delayed on her trip to Riverdale, to take Mr. Weatherbee to the school dance.

Sweet Dreams of Murder - Shield / comic story / 11 pages

Untitled Suzie comic story / 6 pages

Untitled Willy the Wise Guy comic story / 3 pages

Blood Money - Black Hood / comic story / 8 pages

Weeny Roast! Archie / comic story / 10 pages - Archie invites Veronica to a weenie roast, but discovers he has to work his job delivering weenies. When Veronica comes up with the idea of placing an order, so that Archie can deliver it to her, Reggie tries to double cross Archie.

"Yes! This is Katy Keene --- Katy Keene / comic story / 6 pages - Katy has won a date with "The Cinderella Man", which doesn't go down well with her various boy friends.

Is there any mail for me? Li'l Jinx / comic story / 6 pages

The state contends that Jonathan Scott murdered a man... Shield / comic story / 9 pages - Professor Scott has invented a serum that can bring people back from the dead. In order to find out if it works he kills a man but is caught by the police before he can administer the serum. Tried and convicted of murder, he's sentenced to the electric chair. He convinces his assistant Dr. Green to dig up his corpse and inject him with the serum so he can return from the grave to enact his revenge. Professor Scott electrocutes Dr. Ray for turning him in to the police. While trying to kill the district attorney he's stopped by Dusty and kills himself with a lethal injection. Never to return.

Willy the Wise Guy / comic story / 3 pages

Gloomy Gus / comic story / 6 pages

Notes:

The Shield's next appearance is in Mighty Crusaders #1 (1966; Shield II first appears in Fly Man #31);

Dusty's next appearance is in Mighty Crusaders #4 (1966)
Standard Archie Comics mixed bag anthology issue.

The Vulgar Boatman - Archie (8 pages)

Ride or Wrong - Suzie (5 pages)

Hate Raiser - Jughead (6 pages)

Wilbur Comic story (5 pages)

Katy Keene comic story (6 pages) - K.O. trains for a fight. [ this story is reprinted in Suzie Comics 90 ]

1 page Katy Keene paper doll with fashion accessories.

Photo Phinish - Lil Jinx (6 pages)
Suzie story, The Hats in the Fire, reprinted in World of Archie Double Digest 45
Suzie story, Forever Umbrella, reprinted in World of Archie Double Digest 45
Suzie Story, Two Way Stretch, reprinted in World of Archie Double Digest 45
Suzie Story, Suit Yourself, reprinted in World of Archie Double Digest 45
Includes an untitled 4-page Katy Keene story that is reprinted in World of Archie Double Digest #49.

1. "Summer Nights... Winter Days!" (Superman and Batman) written by Paul Kupperberg, penciled by Rich Buckler, inked by Frank McLaughlin, colored by Michele Wolfman and lettered by John Costanza.
  2. "Archer in a Cage" (Green Arrow and Black Canary) written by Mike W. Barr, penciled by Trevor Von Eeden, inked by Larry Mahlstedt, colored by Tom Ziuko and lettered by Bernard Jr.
  3. "Soul Shriek!" (Zatanna) written by Gerry Conway, penciled and inked by Dan Spiegle, colored by Bob LeRose and lettered by John Costanza.
  4. "Matter...Matter Everywhere!" (Hawkman) written by Bob Rozakis, penciled by Alex Saviuk, inked by Rodin Rodriguez, colored by Bob LeRose and lettered by Phil Felix.
  5. "The Snatching of Billy Batson!" (Captain Marvel) written by E. Nelson Bridwell, penciled by Don Newton, inked by Dan Adkins, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Todd Klein.
  6. "DC Profile #86 - Gaspar Saladino" by Michael C. Carmichael.
  7. "Daily Planet" Volume 81 Issue 15 for the month of October 1981 edited by Bob Rozakis, production by Jodi Saviuk and lettered by Typeset. Featuring a Flash of Earth- and Earth-2 team up in The Flash #305. Plus, a World's Finest reprinted adventures of Superman and Batman team ups and a special Dr. Fate team up in The Best of DC Digest #20. The Justice League of America travel back in time to the wild west in Justice League of America #198. "Len's Line-up" features the continued adventures of the New Teen Titans and the Doom Patrol team up in The New Teen Titans #15. Wonder Woman teams up with the New Teen Titans and a Huntress backup feature in Wonder Woman #287. More exciting adventures of the All-Star Squadron in All-Star Squadron #5. And, finally two Dial H" for Hero stories in Adventure Comics #489.
  8. "Hembeck" by Fred Hembeck.

Notes:

  • 48 pages no ads.
  • Net Arrow used.
  • Iris West Allen cameo headshot appearance in the Hawkman story.
name: Summer Nights... Winter Days! / Archer in a Cage / Soul Shriek! / Matter...Matter Everywhere! / The Snatching of Billy Batson!
